	<a name="106304041803850621">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<h1>Computer Technology</h1><br /><h2>Grid Computing</h2><a href="http://www.computerworld.com/printthis/2003/0,4814,84611,00.html"><strong>HP to grid-enable all systems, offers grid services - Computerworld</strong></a>.&nbsp; Grids are Us.&nbsp; This is interesting.&nbsp; I don't quite know how this plays out in the small, but it would be interesting to have Grid capability on a LAN system and see how that supports distribution of services and access to resources on LAN nodes.&nbsp; Just something I am curious about, especially for distributed operation of Miser.<br>
