	<div class="posts">
	<a name="106296068717401077">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.acm.org/sigmod/record/issues/0112/index.html">SIGMOD Record - web edition / December 2001</a>.&nbsp; This is a special issue on Data Mining for Intrusion Detection and Threat Analysis.&nbsp; I suppose the date is significant, and also this is becoming increasingly important even for protecting a single system.  I just downloaded SpyBot-Search&Destroy because of my concern that my Firewall (ZAP) does not tell me enough or handle everything.  I also have some background tasks that are sucking the cycles out of my applications (apparently the Windows installer and Norton Antivirus roaming over the hard drive).&nbsp; I just want more assurance that I know who is doing what and why.<br>
